comments.content: Hello! Does anyone know the name of this particular font? Thank you!!
Does anyone know the name of this particular font? Thank you!!

Three different ornamented styles from the early 19th century. Some foundries packaged different styled fancy letters and numbers in an alphabet fantastique. Off hand, I don't recall a digital font with any these particular numbers. Your source is perhaps based on 19th century clip art?  
Don

For the 0, Dusty Circus is somewhat similar [http://www.fontshop.com/fonts/downloads/baseline\_fonts/dusty\_circus\_fami...](http://web.archive.org/web/20140307083440/http:/www.fontshop.com/fonts/downloads/baseline_fonts/dusty_circus_family_ot/mix "http://www.fontshop.com/fonts/downloads/baseline\_fonts/dusty\_circus\_family\_ot/mix") Also JF Ringmaster [http://www.dafont.com/font-comment.php?file=jf\_ringmaster&text=201&fpp=5...](http://web.archive.org/web/20140307083440/http:/www.dafont.com/font-comment.php?file=jf_ringmaster&text=201&fpp=50&psize=l "http://www.dafont.com/font-comment.php?file=jf\_ringmaster&text=201&fpp=50&psize=l")  
Also Main Strike [http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontmesa/main-strike/](http://web.archive.org/web/20140307083440/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontmesa/main-strike/ "http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontmesa/main-strike/"), Apple Pie [http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontmesa/apple-pie/](http://web.archive.org/web/20140307083440/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontmesa/apple-pie/ "http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontmesa/apple-pie/").  
For the 1, Conestoga is somewhat similar. [http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontmesa/conestoga/](http://web.archive.org/web/20140307083440/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontmesa/conestoga/ "http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/fontmesa/conestoga/")  
don
